06/08/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- New storms hit Bulgaria and Romania on Saturday (5 July), causing electricity and phone service cuts and widespread damage.
According to local media reports, two people were killed and three others were injured after violent storms in Buzau, central Romania.
In neighbouring Bulgaria, heavy rain flooded parts of Sofia on Saturday, knocking down trees.
Damage and power cuts were reported in the north as well.
(Darik, Jurnalul National - 06/08/06)
